Claims We claim: 1. A system for forming a woody biomass component and a binder component into a solid fuel element having a predetermined density, the system comprising: a mixer assembly for mixing the woody biomass component and the binder component in predetermined proportions to provide an uncompressed mixture; a first compression assembly comprising a first cylinder comprising a first chamber therein and a first piston movable in the first cylinder, for compressing the uncompressed mixture in the first chamber to provide a first compressed mixture formed into a preliminary element occupying a first volume, the preliminary element having a preliminary density; a fine meter assembly for delivering at least one predetermined amount of the uncompressed mixture to the first chamber; and a second compression assembly comprising a second cylinder comprising a second chamber therein and a second piston movable in the second cylinder, for compressing the preliminary element in the second chamber to provide a final compressed mixture formed into the solid fuel element occupying a second volume that is less than the first volume, the solid fuel element having the predetermined density, the predetermined density being greater than the preliminary density. 2. The system according to claim 1 comprising a plurality of heat-generating elements for heating the uncompressed mixture and the first compressed mixture to at least one preselected temperature that is less than a melting temperature of the binder component. 3. The system according to claim 1 in which the compression of the preliminary element to form the solid fuel element is a substantially adiabatic process in which the final compressed mixture is heated to a predetermined temperature that is at least equal to the melting temperature of the binder component. The system according to claim 1 in which the mixer assembly comprises: a mixer housing extending between input and output ends thereof, the mixer housing defining a mixer cavity therein, and additionally comprising an input opening at the input end and an output opening at the output end in communication with the mixer cavity; and a mixer auger at least partially located in the mixer cavity and rotatable about a longitudinal axis thereof, for mixing the woody biomass component and the binder component together in the mixer cavity and moving the woody biomass component and the binder component from the input end to the output end as they are mixed together, to form the uncompressed mixture at the output end. The system according to claim 4 in which the fine meter assembly comprises: a hopper, in which the uncompressed mixture is receivable; and an auger subassembly, for drawing the uncompressed mixture from the hopper and delivering said at least one predetermined amount thereof to the first chamber. The system according to claim 5 in which the fine meter assembly comprises a fine meter assembly controller which controls the auger subassembly based on the second volume of the solid fuel element. The system according to claim 6 additionally comprising: an intermediate feed control assembly comprising: a sensor in the hopper, for sensing that the hopper is vacated; an intermediate feed control chamber positioned below the output opening, to permit the uncompressed mixture to fall into the intermediate feed control chamber under the influence of gravity; an upper gate movable between a closed position, in which the upper gate prevents the uncompressed material from falling from the output opening into the intermediate feed control chamber, and an open position, 

 in which the mixer cavity is in fluid communication with the intermediate feed control chamber; a lower gate movable between a closed position, in which the lower gate partially defines the intermediate feed control chamber, and an open position, in which the uncompressed mixture located in the intermediate feed control chamber is permitted to exit therefrom to the hopper under the influence of gravity; and a controller for controlling movement of the upper and lower gates, the controller being configured for moving the upper gate to the open position thereof and for moving the lower gate to the closed position thereof upon receiving a signal from the sensor indicating that the hopper is empty, and the controller being further configured to close the upper gate and to open the lower gate when a predetermined intermediate amount of the uncompressed mixture is in the intermediate feed control chamber, the predetermined intermediate amount being receivable in the hopper. 8. The system according to claim 4 additionally comprising: a woody biomass processor, for forming the woody biomass component into a plurality of woody biomass particles of woody biomass having a predetermined woody biomass particle size distribution; and a binder processor, for forming the binder component into particles of binder having a predetermined binder particle size distribution. 9. A method of forming a solid fuel element having a predetermined density comprising a woody biomass component and a binder component, the method comprising: (a) providing the woody biomass component, the woody biomass component comprising woody biomass particles having a predetermined woody biomass particle size distribution; (b) providing the binder component, the binder component comprising binder particles having a predetermined binder particle size distribution; 

 (c) mixing the woody biomass component and the binder component together in predetermined proportions relative to each other to provide an uncompressed mixture; (d) providing a first compression assembly comprising a first cylinder comprising a first chamber therein and a first piston movable in the first cylinder; (e) via a fine metering assembly, delivering at least one predetermined amount of the uncompressed mixture to the first chamber; (f) with the first compression assembly, compressing said at least one predetermined amount of the uncompressed mixture to provide a preliminary element comprising a first compressed mixture having a preliminary density; (g) providing a second compression assembly comprising a second cylinder comprising a second chamber therein and a second piston movable in the second cylinder; (h) positioning the preliminary element in the second chamber; (i) compressing the preliminary element in the second chamber to form the solid fuel element having the predetermined density, the predetermined density being greater than the preliminary density; and (j) removing the solid fuel element from the second chamber. 10. The method according to claim 9 in which the predetermined proportions in step (c) comprise: at least about 70% and at most about 80% by weight of the woody biomass component; and at least about 20% and at most about 30% by weight of the binder component. 1 1. The method of claim 9 in which, in step (c), the uncompressed mixture has a predetermined moisture content. 12. The method of claim 9 in which, in step (c), the uncompressed mixture is heated to a preselected temperature below a melting temperature of the binder component. 13. The method of claim 9 in which, in step (e), the uncompressed mixture is heated to a preselected temperature below a melting temperature of the binder component. 14. The method of claim 9 in which, in step (f), the first compression assembly maintains a temperature of the uncompressed mixture in the first chamber at a preselected temperature that is below a melting temperature of the binder component. 15. The method according to claim 9 in which step (i) is a substantially adiabatic process in which, during the compression of the preliminary element in the second chamber, the preliminary element is heated to a predetermined temperature that is at least equal to a melting temperature of the binder component. 16. The method according to claim 9 in which said at least one predetermined amount of the uncompressed material is delivered to the first chamber in three separately delivered portions, and each said portion is compressed in the first chamber consecutively to form the preliminary element. 17. The method of claim 9 in which, in step (f), the uncompressed mixture is subjected to a first compression force of approximately 3.15 tonne per square meter (approximately 2 long tons per square inch) in the first chamber for a first compression period. 18. The method of claim 9 in which, in step (i), the preliminary element is subjected to a second compression force of approximately 4.275 tonne per square meter (approximately 3 long tons per square inch) in the second chamber for a second compression period. 19. A solid fuel element formed according to the method of claim 9 comprising: a core portion; and a plurality of lobes extending radially from the core portion. 20. The solid fuel element of claim 19 formed to have a consistent heat signature during combustion. 21. The solid fuel element of claim 19 in which the lobes are spaced radially equidistantly from each other around the core portion. 22. A system for forming a woody biomass component and a binder component into a solid fuel element having a predetermined density, the system comprising: a first compression assembly for compressing an uncompressed mixture of the woody biomass component and the binder component to provide a preliminary element having a preliminary density; and a second compression assembly for compressing the preliminary element to form the preliminary element into the solid fuel element having the predetermined density, the predetermined density being greater than the preliminary density. 23. A method of forming a solid fuel element having a predetermined density comprising a woody biomass component and a binder component, the method comprising: (a) with a first compression assembly, compressing an uncompressed mixture of the woody biomass component and the binder component to provide a preliminary element having a preliminary density; (b) with a second compression assembly, compressing the preliminary element to form the preliminary element into the solid fuel element having the predetermined density, the predetermined density being greater than the preliminary density; and (c) removing the solid fuel element from the second compression assembly.
